[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0: Bolivia and Peru, at elevations of 1,500 m (4,900 ft) to 5,000 m (16,400
[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0: ft).  It is solid green, darker above and lighter below, with some blue
[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0: visible on the wings when flying.  It has a pale bill and medium length
[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0: tail.  It is stockier and darker than the mountain parakeet.
[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0:
[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0: Most flocks are small, but sometimes include over 300 individuals. The
[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0: Andean parakeet eats seeds, buds, and berries, and it breeds in burrows in
[10:12] <dalek> parrot/smoke-me/8.1.0: steep banks.
